1:01:26.960 --> 1:01:28.126
We're floating.

1:01:29.460 --> 1:01:30.794
We're breathing.

1:01:30.877 --> 1:01:33.960
We're in a calm, neutral space.

1:01:34.043 --> 1:01:37.377
No one is angry. No one is sick.

1:01:42.919 --> 1:01:44.043
(EXHALES)

1:01:46.293 --> 1:01:47.377
(WHISPERING) Um...

1:01:49.418 --> 1:01:50.752
Okay, I, uh...

1:01:53.585 --> 1:01:56.710
Uh, this isn't... Oh.

1:01:56.794 --> 1:01:59.335
-♪ (MUSIC STOPS) ♪
-This is so weird.

1:02:03.627 --> 1:02:08.043
I'm sorry. I'm-- I'm--
I'm so, so sorry, but, uh...

1:02:08.126 --> 1:02:10.585
I-- I don't know
if I can keep doing this.

1:02:14.377 --> 1:02:18.460
No. Let me explain. Let me...

1:02:18.543 --> 1:02:22.460
Let me try to explain.
I owe you that...

1:02:22.543 --> 1:02:25.835
because this morning,
I saw something on the news,

1:02:25.919 --> 1:02:28.293
except it's not just that.
It's-- it's everything

1:02:28.377 --> 1:02:30.710
that's been happening
to all of us.

1:02:30.794 --> 1:02:33.502
It's-- Okay. Hold on.

1:02:34.877 --> 1:02:36.251
-♪ (TRANQUIL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(EXHALES)

1:02:36.335 --> 1:02:37.960
Let me start from the beginning.

1:02:39.085 --> 1:02:42.168
(SIGHS)
When the virus first appeared,

1:02:42.251 --> 1:02:44.710
like all of you, I was frantic.

1:02:44.794 --> 1:02:46.919
I-- I didn't know
what was going on,

1:02:47.001 --> 1:02:50.168
so I decided to fly home
to Wisconsin

1:02:50.251 --> 1:02:53.710
and isolate with my family.
I know. I know.

1:02:54.502 --> 1:02:55.919
But I'm a hopeful person,

1:02:56.001 --> 1:02:59.418
and I just wanted to see
if it was possible,

1:02:59.502 --> 1:03:02.418
if just maybe we could use
this terrible illness

1:03:02.502 --> 1:03:04.001
as-- as some sort of...

1:03:05.043 --> 1:03:08.001
gift, uh... a timeout

1:03:08.085 --> 1:03:11.335
to heal and bond.
I know. I know.

1:03:12.752 --> 1:03:17.043
But I love my family,
and I just thought, "What if?"

1:03:19.418 --> 1:03:22.126
My folks still live
in Lake Auburn,

1:03:22.210 --> 1:03:23.502
this tiny little town,

1:03:23.585 --> 1:03:25.835
it's like 8,000 people
and change,

1:03:25.919 --> 1:03:27.960
in the farmhouse
where I grew up

1:03:28.043 --> 1:03:31.669
and where the Montgomerys
have lived for five generations.

1:03:31.752 --> 1:03:34.960
I always love it... (LAUGHS)
...when a couple on HGTV

1:03:35.043 --> 1:03:37.126
is renovating
their Craftsman-style home

1:03:37.210 --> 1:03:39.251
and they demand
a farmhouse sink,

1:03:39.335 --> 1:03:40.627
"We have to have
a farmhouse sink,"

1:03:40.710 --> 1:03:44.293
because you know what we call
that in Lake Auburn? A sink.

1:03:44.377 --> 1:03:48.085
(CHUCKLES) And as I'm driving
through town,

1:03:48.168 --> 1:03:50.460
I-- I notice something.

1:03:50.543 --> 1:03:53.377
No one is social distancing
or wearing a mask.

1:03:54.877 --> 1:03:58.502
So maybe this is a refuge,
a-- a safe zone.

1:03:58.585 --> 1:04:01.293
How great,
how potentially great.

1:04:01.377 --> 1:04:03.794
And-- and I pull into
our driveway,

1:04:03.877 --> 1:04:06.418
and there's a Trump sign
on the lawn,

1:04:07.085 --> 1:04:08.877
but I tell myself, "No."

1:04:08.960 --> 1:04:12.669
Stop. Lower your knee-jerk
liberal defense mechanism

1:04:12.752 --> 1:04:15.669
because that sign
isn't automatically hateful.

1:04:15.752 --> 1:04:19.794
It's not a Confederate flag
like last Christmas on the tree.

1:04:22.043 --> 1:04:25.877
I go inside,
and I hug my parents

1:04:25.960 --> 1:04:28.251
and my five
brothers and sisters,

1:04:28.335 --> 1:04:30.919
which feels so good, except...

1:04:32.001 --> 1:04:34.752
almost all of them
are wearing MAGA hats.

1:04:35.585 --> 1:04:37.168
Even the dog.

1:04:37.251 --> 1:04:40.210
"No," I tell myself, "stop it.

1:04:40.293 --> 1:04:43.627
They're just hats. Calm down."
And I'm offered one.

1:04:44.960 --> 1:04:46.919
And it's on my head.

1:04:47.001 --> 1:04:48.377
And everyone is chanting

1:04:48.460 --> 1:04:51.085
and-- and my brother Ned
reaches into my chest,

1:04:51.168 --> 1:04:53.377
and he pulls out my heart,
and they eat it.

1:04:53.460 --> 1:04:56.377
No. Stop it, Clarissa.
Stop exaggerating!

1:04:56.460 --> 1:04:59.085
But I can't.
There are tater tots!

1:04:59.168 --> 1:05:02.085
♪ (TRANQUIL MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

1:05:03.543 --> 1:05:07.877
So... (SIGHS) I'm with my family

1:05:07.960 --> 1:05:11.210
and I am trying so hard
not to be a snob,

1:05:11.293 --> 1:05:15.669
because it's not a horror movie
or Stephen King.

1:05:15.752 --> 1:05:18.210
And then my Uncle Dirk says,

1:05:18.293 --> 1:05:20.043
"Trump's a real
straight shooter.

1:05:20.126 --> 1:05:23.377
Tells it like it is."
And I'm drowning.

1:05:23.460 --> 1:05:25.919
I'm choking. I--
I try to say something,

1:05:26.001 --> 1:05:27.960
but only random words come out.

1:05:28.043 --> 1:05:29.418
It's like I'm in The Exorcist.

1:05:29.502 --> 1:05:33.543
"Charlottesville,
Obamagate, golf!"

1:05:33.627 --> 1:05:36.377
And-- and my mom grabs me
and pulls me into the kitchen.

1:05:36.460 --> 1:05:39.418
She knows me, so she says,
"Stop it, Clarissa.

1:05:39.502 --> 1:05:42.043
Right now,
you're driving yourself crazy.

1:05:42.752 --> 1:05:44.210
We are so happy to see you,

1:05:44.293 --> 1:05:46.585
but I'm not sure
what you're doing here.

1:05:46.669 --> 1:05:48.710
This whole corona
whatever-the-heck-it-is

1:05:48.794 --> 1:05:49.710
is a hoax.

1:05:49.794 --> 1:05:51.418
It's just like
that impeachment doohickey,

1:05:51.502 --> 1:05:53.418
or that Russia whatchamadoozie,

1:05:53.502 --> 1:05:56.752
or-- or the idea that Melania
speaks with a foreign accent.

1:05:56.835 --> 1:05:58.168
She's from Maine."

1:06:00.293 --> 1:06:03.418
And I have no idea
what to say to that.

1:06:03.502 --> 1:06:07.460
And-- and she keeps going.
She says, "No one here is sick.

1:06:07.543 --> 1:06:09.835
Well, sure,
your sister's on methadone,

1:06:09.919 --> 1:06:12.377
and Randy lost a finger
in that snowmobile accident,

1:06:12.460 --> 1:06:14.251
and your cousin Brittany
has a little cough

1:06:14.335 --> 1:06:16.126
from working
at the fulfillment center,

1:06:16.210 --> 1:06:17.335
but we're fine.

1:06:17.418 --> 1:06:18.627
And have you ever thought

1:06:18.710 --> 1:06:21.001
that maybe there is
some kind of disease,

1:06:21.085 --> 1:06:24.627
but that it's all happening
in New York and California

1:06:24.710 --> 1:06:27.502
and maybe that's because
all of you are so upset?"

1:06:29.710 --> 1:06:32.418
(CHUCKLES) And--
and maybe she's not crazy.

1:06:33.377 --> 1:06:35.627
Maybe she's not wrong,
so I listen,

1:06:35.710 --> 1:06:37.377
and she says, "Think about it.

1:06:38.877 --> 1:06:41.126
You wanted an enemy,
so you made one up.

1:06:41.210 --> 1:06:44.502
It's like with climate change.
If it snows in New York,

1:06:44.585 --> 1:06:47.210
you commission a study,
you write 58 op-ed pieces,

1:06:47.293 --> 1:06:50.293
and you blame it on us.
If it snows out here,

1:06:50.377 --> 1:06:51.794
we put on a sweater."

1:06:54.502 --> 1:06:57.460
And she's actually making sense,
and I'm calming down,

1:06:57.543 --> 1:07:00.001
and she hands me a cup of tea,
and she says,

1:07:00.085 --> 1:07:03.335
"And we're not racist.
That's nonsense.

1:07:03.418 --> 1:07:05.627
There aren't any Black people
here in Lake Auburn,

1:07:05.710 --> 1:07:07.293
so who would we be racist to?"

1:07:10.752 --> 1:07:11.752
She said that.

1:07:12.585 --> 1:07:13.835
And then she says,

1:07:13.919 --> 1:07:17.210
"And please don't lecture me
about pronouns,

1:07:17.293 --> 1:07:19.043
because I'll admit it,
I don't understand

1:07:19.126 --> 1:07:23.168
all that transgender, nonbinary,
LGBTQ business,

1:07:23.251 --> 1:07:26.085
so I just call everyone 'dear.'
Done."

1:07:28.210 --> 1:07:33.210
Which is almost sweet,
so I smile and she takes my hand

1:07:33.293 --> 1:07:37.502
and she says,
"And real soon, like tomorrow,

1:07:37.585 --> 1:07:41.794
this whole virus hoo-ha,
it's all going to be over.

1:07:42.752 --> 1:07:44.168
Just like President Trump said,

1:07:44.251 --> 1:07:47.460
it's gonna be like a miracle,
and it's gone.

1:07:48.794 --> 1:07:50.126
Why can't you believe him?

1:07:50.210 --> 1:07:53.168
He's given us
the best economy ever,

1:07:53.251 --> 1:07:55.752
and it's coming right back.

1:07:55.835 --> 1:07:59.335
I love you, sweetheart,
but you need to have faith."

1:08:03.126 --> 1:08:04.627
And in that moment, I...

1:08:06.293 --> 1:08:07.960
I want to believe her.

1:08:08.043 --> 1:08:11.043
I want it so badly, because...

1:08:13.251 --> 1:08:14.377
she's my mom.

1:08:17.043 --> 1:08:19.335
And so I start
really thinking about it.

1:08:21.126 --> 1:08:22.502
What if I met him?

1:08:24.001 --> 1:08:25.335
What would I say?

1:08:26.585 --> 1:08:29.794
Would I just sputter and scream?

1:08:31.502 --> 1:08:32.710
What if he listened?

1:08:34.335 --> 1:08:35.502
What if I listened?

1:08:36.627 --> 1:08:38.251
What if everyone
in this country,

1:08:38.335 --> 1:08:43.126
what if we all just stopped
being so angry and listened?

1:08:48.877 --> 1:08:52.960
So, I leave the kitchen,
and I look around at my family,

1:08:53.043 --> 1:08:56.543
and they're all smiling,
and I think...

1:08:58.293 --> 1:09:01.043
"Maybe this is possible.
Maybe this can work."

1:09:01.126 --> 1:09:02.710
And then my brother Travis says,

1:09:02.794 --> 1:09:05.210
"Clarissa, you know what's wrong
with you?

1:09:05.794 --> 1:09:07.502
You've got TDS."

1:09:08.168 --> 1:09:10.293
And I ask, "What's that?"

1:09:10.377 --> 1:09:13.210
And he says,
"Trump Derangement Syndrome!"

1:09:13.293 --> 1:09:16.710
(LAUGHS)
And they're all laughing...

1:09:18.085 --> 1:09:19.502
and it's like Rosemary's Baby

1:09:19.585 --> 1:09:21.251
if the Satanists
all had corndogs,

1:09:21.335 --> 1:09:23.001
and before I know it,
I'm crying,

1:09:23.085 --> 1:09:24.752
and I blurt out, "I can't!

1:09:24.835 --> 1:09:27.293
I can't do this.
I love you all so much,

1:09:27.377 --> 1:09:29.710
and I don't want to hate you
or argue with you

1:09:29.794 --> 1:09:32.335
or just grit my teeth and pass
the gravy boat and say,

1:09:32.418 --> 1:09:35.126
'No, actually, Canada doesn't
have nuclear weapons.'

1:09:35.210 --> 1:09:37.001
I can't act as if
there are two sides

1:09:37.085 --> 1:09:38.502
to questions
that don't have two sides.

1:09:38.585 --> 1:09:39.919
And Mom,
I know you're going to say

1:09:40.001 --> 1:09:41.669
I'm choosing politics
over family,

1:09:41.752 --> 1:09:43.669
and maybe I am, but I can't!

1:09:43.752 --> 1:09:44.919
I can't be here!"

1:09:47.960 --> 1:09:50.585
And my dad drives me
to the airport,

1:09:50.669 --> 1:09:52.502
and when we pull up
outside the terminal,

1:09:52.585 --> 1:09:55.168
he says, "Hold on.
I have to tell you something."

1:09:55.251 --> 1:09:59.168
And this is the weirdest thing
of all, because my dad...

1:09:59.251 --> 1:10:02.251
he doesn't talk.
I mean, not ever.

1:10:02.335 --> 1:10:05.418
He-- he's a contractor
and a vet and a really good guy,

1:10:05.502 --> 1:10:07.168
but he's not chatty,
or huggy, or--

1:10:07.251 --> 1:10:09.669
Okay, he's the sort of person
who, if he's not interested,

1:10:09.752 --> 1:10:12.710
he shuts his eyes
and falls asleep sitting up...

1:10:12.794 --> 1:10:17.377
except for right now,
because he's looking right at me

1:10:17.460 --> 1:10:19.502
to make sure
I'm paying attention,

1:10:20.543 --> 1:10:21.627
and he says...

1:10:23.335 --> 1:10:27.377
"I have to tell you something
because I have to tell someone,

1:10:27.460 --> 1:10:30.377
and if you tell your mom
or anyone else, I swear to God,

1:10:30.460 --> 1:10:34.001
I'll deny it till my dying day,
and I'll kill you...

1:10:36.126 --> 1:10:37.919
but I'm not voting for him.

1:10:39.085 --> 1:10:40.251
Not this time. I can't.

1:10:40.335 --> 1:10:43.251
And it's not about the virus
or collusion or whatever."

1:10:43.335 --> 1:10:44.418
And I say...

1:10:45.585 --> 1:10:46.794
(WHISPERING) "Dad."

1:10:47.752 --> 1:10:48.960
"Dad." And he says...

1:10:50.126 --> 1:10:51.752
"John McCain.

1:10:53.460 --> 1:10:57.377
He flew 23 missions,
and then he got shot down

1:10:57.460 --> 1:11:00.168
and held prisoner
for five and a half years.

1:11:00.251 --> 1:11:02.168
He was starved and beaten

1:11:02.251 --> 1:11:04.126
so badly that
for the rest of his life,

1:11:04.210 --> 1:11:07.043
he couldn't raise his arms
over his head,

1:11:07.126 --> 1:11:11.085
and Trump, he said, 'I like guys
who weren't captured.'"

1:11:11.168 --> 1:11:14.460
And-- and I have never seen
my dad like this.

1:11:14.543 --> 1:11:17.460
It is pouring out of him.
He-- he-- he said,

1:11:17.543 --> 1:11:21.502
"Trump kept insulting the man
even after he died.

1:11:21.585 --> 1:11:23.502
Trump was making some
goddamn appearance,

1:11:23.585 --> 1:11:25.335
grinning like a baboon.
He was in front of

1:11:25.418 --> 1:11:28.210
a naval destroyer
named the John McCain,

1:11:28.293 --> 1:11:30.669
but Trump had them cover up
the name."

1:11:32.418 --> 1:11:33.877
And he stops...

1:11:34.835 --> 1:11:37.585
because
he's so furious or appalled

1:11:37.669 --> 1:11:40.460
but I-- I mean,
I have never heard my dad

1:11:40.543 --> 1:11:43.960
say this many words in a row,
but he holds up his hand,

1:11:44.043 --> 1:11:46.126
because he's not finished yet.
He-- he says,

1:11:46.210 --> 1:11:48.126
"I-- I didn't always agree
with McCain.

1:11:48.210 --> 1:11:49.960
Hell, I don't even know
if I liked him,

1:11:50.043 --> 1:11:52.377
but the man was a hero.

1:11:52.460 --> 1:11:55.627
An American hero,
and Trump's a rich boy,

1:11:55.710 --> 1:11:58.168
a five-time draft dodger
with bone spurs,

1:11:58.251 --> 1:11:59.669
and I don't even care
about that.

1:11:59.752 --> 1:12:01.377
I care about McCain."

1:12:06.543 --> 1:12:08.210
So, I hug him...

1:12:10.835 --> 1:12:14.585
and I get back on the plane,
and I fly here to Vermont,

1:12:14.669 --> 1:12:16.960
and I think,
"I'll just keep making...

1:12:17.043 --> 1:12:20.085
my meditation videos
to help people."

1:12:22.210 --> 1:12:24.710
Except I can't stop thinking
about my dad.

1:12:26.752 --> 1:12:29.085
I can't stop thinking
about everything.

1:12:31.251 --> 1:12:37.877
CROWD: (CHANTING) USA! USA!
USA! USA! USA! USA!

1:12:40.460 --> 1:12:41.710
(CHANTING FADES)

1:12:42.752 --> 1:12:45.585
I live in Wyoming,
where we've been lucky.

1:12:46.752 --> 1:12:49.251
They needed nurses in New York.

1:12:49.335 --> 1:12:52.168
My best friend, Kendra,
was volunteering.

1:12:52.251 --> 1:12:55.001
And I was--
I was really scared...

1:12:55.085 --> 1:12:58.877
but Kendra said Wyoming
is so boring, so... (CHUCKLES)

1:13:00.085 --> 1:13:02.210
Here-- here I am.

1:13:02.293 --> 1:13:04.794
It's-- it's just like
everybody says.

1:13:06.835 --> 1:13:08.669
Even the New York
doctors and nurses,

1:13:08.752 --> 1:13:10.794
they've never seen...

1:13:10.877 --> 1:13:12.835
they've never seen
anything like it.

1:13:15.251 --> 1:13:17.126
(KISSES TEETH) Uh, I just...

1:13:17.960 --> 1:13:20.126
I just got off a 14-hour shift,

1:13:20.210 --> 1:13:23.627
and I know I should probably

1:13:23.710 --> 1:13:26.543
take off my clothes,
put 'em in a plastic bag,

1:13:26.627 --> 1:13:27.960
take a shower.

1:13:28.043 --> 1:13:30.251
It's just all so surreal.

1:13:33.960 --> 1:13:35.960
Mostly because
of this one patient...

1:13:38.043 --> 1:13:39.085
Miriam.

1:13:42.085 --> 1:13:43.335
I first met her, like...

1:13:44.919 --> 1:13:46.126
three weeks ago.

1:13:47.168 --> 1:13:50.043
I was working in the tent
outside the hospital

1:13:50.126 --> 1:13:51.418
doing nasal swabs,

1:13:51.502 --> 1:13:55.752
and she's all dressed up...

1:13:55.835 --> 1:14:02.335
and she's got this amazing shawl
and lipstick, and I said...

1:14:03.627 --> 1:14:05.210
"I-- I-- I like your bracelet."

1:14:05.293 --> 1:14:07.710
And she says,
"Oh, thanks. Isn't it pretty?

1:14:07.794 --> 1:14:10.502
My-- my son got it for me
after I told him to."

1:14:11.752 --> 1:14:14.043
And I said, "Are-- are--
are you headed somewhere else?"

1:14:14.126 --> 1:14:16.293
And she said, "No, I just wanted
to look nice

1:14:16.377 --> 1:14:18.585
for the doctors and nurses."

1:14:18.669 --> 1:14:20.502
And I said, "That--
that's awesome."

1:14:21.502 --> 1:14:23.001
And then she says, "I'm Jewish."

1:14:23.710 --> 1:14:25.669
And then I went, "Oh, uh...

1:14:25.752 --> 1:14:27.877
Nazel tok."  (LAUGHS)

1:14:29.251 --> 1:14:32.043
And then she says,
"You'll get there."

1:14:34.043 --> 1:14:37.877
She's smart and funny.

1:14:39.043 --> 1:14:40.960
(CHUCKLES)
After I stuck the swab

1:14:41.043 --> 1:14:43.251
all the way up her nose,
she said,

1:14:43.335 --> 1:14:46.043
she said,
"Thank you and fuck you."

1:14:47.126 --> 1:14:50.627
(CHUCKLES) And we laughed.

1:14:50.710 --> 1:14:55.543
And her temperature was 99.8,
so the doctor sends her home,

1:14:55.627 --> 1:14:57.752
tells her to monitor
her symptoms.

1:14:58.543 --> 1:15:00.293
And she says, "I know. I know.

1:15:00.377 --> 1:15:03.251
My daughter's a neurologist
in Seattle."

1:15:03.335 --> 1:15:05.794
And she turns to go,
and then she turns back

1:15:05.877 --> 1:15:08.210
and says, "Single."

1:15:08.293 --> 1:15:10.627
And then she turns to go,
and then she turns back

1:15:10.710 --> 1:15:12.877
and says, "Again."

1:15:13.752 --> 1:15:15.085
(CHUCKLES)

1:15:17.710 --> 1:15:19.669
Uh...

1:15:19.752 --> 1:15:24.251
The next time I see her,
um, I'm working the ER

1:15:25.043 --> 1:15:26.752
and she's being admitted...

1:15:27.877 --> 1:15:30.085
'cause she's up to 102
and coughing.

1:15:31.669 --> 1:15:32.752
Not-- not terrible,

1:15:32.835 --> 1:15:36.085
but the doctor just wants to do
a chest X-ray,

1:15:36.168 --> 1:15:40.960
and Miriam,
she-- she remembers me.

1:15:41.043 --> 1:15:43.085
And she says,
"You're from Wyoming, right?"

1:15:43.168 --> 1:15:44.085
And I said, "Yeah."

1:15:44.168 --> 1:15:46.418
And she says,
"So you weren't kidding."

1:15:47.293 --> 1:15:49.502
(CHUCKLES)
And then I hand her a gown,

1:15:49.585 --> 1:15:51.627
and then she says,
"Before this goes any further,

1:15:51.710 --> 1:15:53.251
I need to ask you something.

1:15:53.919 --> 1:15:55.418
Are you a Republican?"

1:15:57.210 --> 1:15:59.543
And I said, um...

1:15:59.627 --> 1:16:02.251
"No. Uh, I guess...

1:16:03.251 --> 1:16:05.126
I guess I'm--
I'm an Independent."

1:16:07.460 --> 1:16:11.377
And then she just stares at me
like Darth Vader

1:16:11.460 --> 1:16:13.877
and just says, "Oy."

1:16:13.960 --> 1:16:15.627
(CHUCKLES)

1:16:15.710 --> 1:16:17.877
And I-- I ask her
what that means,

1:16:17.960 --> 1:16:21.585
and she just says, "It means
that if you say that any louder,

1:16:21.669 --> 1:16:24.168
everyone in the tri-state area
will kill you."

1:16:25.960 --> 1:16:27.585
Her X-ray isn't good...

1:16:28.752 --> 1:16:30.627
but she's not showing
any advanced symptoms,

1:16:30.710 --> 1:16:33.168
but the doctor just wants to
find her a bed for observation

1:16:33.251 --> 1:16:35.627
and start her on
this experimental protocol.

1:16:37.085 --> 1:16:42.710
And she says, "You mean that--
that hydro-whatever-it-is?

1:16:42.794 --> 1:16:44.585
That-- that Trump bullshit?"

1:16:44.669 --> 1:16:47.043
And I said, "Yes, Miriam.

1:16:47.126 --> 1:16:48.919
It says right here
on the IV drip,

1:16:49.001 --> 1:16:53.251
'550 CCs of Trump Bullshit
every hour.'"

1:16:53.335 --> 1:16:55.251
And then she says,
"Oh, it's just like Fox News."

1:16:55.335 --> 1:16:57.418
And then I said, "Yeah, well,
maybe it'll start working."

1:16:57.502 --> 1:16:59.460
And she says,
"And that's what his parents

1:16:59.543 --> 1:17:00.710
said about Jared."

1:17:03.627 --> 1:17:04.794
She's tough.

1:17:06.335 --> 1:17:07.502
She's tough.

1:17:08.669 --> 1:17:10.794
I told her, I said-- I said...

1:17:12.418 --> 1:17:14.710
"I've never met
anyone like you."

1:17:16.126 --> 1:17:17.960
And she says, "What, you mean--

1:17:18.043 --> 1:17:19.794
you mean a strong,
independent woman?"

1:17:19.877 --> 1:17:23.377
And I said, "No, so much Kleenex
in your purse."

1:17:26.085 --> 1:17:28.710
(SIGHS) And then she--
she starts coughing,

1:17:28.794 --> 1:17:31.502
and I-- I guess I-- I guess
I must've looked worried,

1:17:31.585 --> 1:17:34.877
and she says, "Well,
let's hope it's cancer."

1:17:34.960 --> 1:17:36.043
(LAUGHS)

1:17:37.710 --> 1:17:41.502
We don't say shit like that
in Wyoming. (LAUGHS)

1:17:44.669 --> 1:17:45.710
(SIGHS)

1:17:47.794 --> 1:17:51.168
And the days are just getting
more and more insane.

1:17:51.251 --> 1:17:53.835
The halls are filled
with patients on gurneys

1:17:53.960 --> 1:17:55.251
waiting for beds.

1:17:56.210 --> 1:17:57.794
We're all wearing more
and more PPE

1:17:57.877 --> 1:18:00.085
when we can get it, and...

1:18:01.877 --> 1:18:05.502
the whole hospital just looks
like a-- a cross between

1:18:05.585 --> 1:18:08.877
a space station and--
and a subway.

1:18:12.710 --> 1:18:16.919
Now we're all just trying
to hold it together 'cause...

1:18:18.960 --> 1:18:21.126
that's what they taught us
in nursing school.

1:18:23.085 --> 1:18:26.085
Do the job, provide comfort...

1:18:29.919 --> 1:18:32.418
because if you start crying,
you'll never stop.

1:18:36.502 --> 1:18:38.835
And one day,
we lose eight people.

1:18:41.418 --> 1:18:45.794
The next day, it's 18, 27...

1:18:49.669 --> 1:18:52.585
and the only thing
that's keeping me going is her.

1:18:54.710 --> 1:18:55.752
Miriam.

1:18:58.919 --> 1:19:00.210
Because she's stable,

1:19:00.293 --> 1:19:03.418
and I-- I keep telling myself
she's gonna make it,

1:19:03.502 --> 1:19:04.960
'cause people are making it.

1:19:06.919 --> 1:19:09.043
And I-- I take her vitals
and she's--

1:19:09.126 --> 1:19:11.001
she's got this terrible look
on her face,

1:19:11.085 --> 1:19:13.168
and I ask,
"Miriam, what's wrong?"

1:19:13.960 --> 1:19:15.085
And she points to the--

1:19:15.168 --> 1:19:16.960
to the TV
hanging up on the wall.

1:19:17.043 --> 1:19:21.418
And it's one of those
White House press briefings,

1:19:21.502 --> 1:19:25.251
and the president's talking
about how great everything is,

1:19:25.335 --> 1:19:27.669
and what an amazing job
he's doing.

1:19:27.752 --> 1:19:30.251
And Miriam's wheezing,
and she says,

1:19:30.335 --> 1:19:33.835
"I need Advil, the bedpan,
and a gun."

1:19:33.919 --> 1:19:36.835
I just said, "Miriam,
we're-- we're turning this off,"

1:19:36.919 --> 1:19:38.627
and she won't give me
the remote,

1:19:38.710 --> 1:19:40.502
and then we both hear him
talking about

1:19:40.585 --> 1:19:42.919
how we can maybe
start injecting ourselves

1:19:43.001 --> 1:19:45.251
with-- with disinfectant
or bleach,

1:19:45.335 --> 1:19:47.752
and she says,
"What is he talkin' about?

1:19:47.835 --> 1:19:49.460
Is he talking
about cleaning products?

1:19:49.543 --> 1:19:51.585
Is-- is it a Jewish disease?"
(CHUCKLES)

1:19:51.669 --> 1:19:52.835
And then she tells me,

1:19:52.919 --> 1:19:56.335
"I need 800 milligrams
of Lemon Pledge, stat."

1:19:59.126 --> 1:20:01.794
And she starts coughing,
and I said,

1:20:01.877 --> 1:20:04.794
"Miriam, you just need to--
you just need to calm down.

1:20:04.877 --> 1:20:07.377
You-- you can't--
you can't watch him."

1:20:07.460 --> 1:20:09.877
And she says,
"Don't you get it?

1:20:09.960 --> 1:20:13.669
My rage is the only thing
that's keeping me alive."

1:20:17.794 --> 1:20:21.001
The doctor comes in and we have
a conversation out in the hall

1:20:21.085 --> 1:20:22.960
about putting Miriam
on a ventilator,

1:20:23.043 --> 1:20:25.627
if we can even find one,

1:20:25.710 --> 1:20:29.919
and I ask him if--
if, you know, maybe she's right.

1:20:31.126 --> 1:20:33.919
Maybe she just needs
to keep talking.

1:20:37.085 --> 1:20:39.460
And then, the next morning,
I get to the hospital

1:20:39.543 --> 1:20:43.752
and there's a refrigerated truck
parked outside

1:20:43.835 --> 1:20:46.251
because there are
so many bodies.

1:20:48.919 --> 1:20:51.919
And I get to Miriam's room,
and she's doing a little better.

1:20:53.293 --> 1:20:56.043
Her cough is intermittent,
she's sipping Pedialyte,

1:20:56.919 --> 1:20:59.752
and she tells me, "Sharynn...

1:21:01.210 --> 1:21:03.502
last night, I had a dream."

1:21:03.585 --> 1:21:07.585
And she says that...
"I dreamed that when I woke up,

1:21:08.293 --> 1:21:09.877
everything was different.

1:21:10.585 --> 1:21:13.001
People were still sick, but...

1:21:13.085 --> 1:21:16.335
everyone wasn't fighting
or calling each other names

1:21:16.418 --> 1:21:19.293
or blaming everything
on the Chinese

1:21:19.377 --> 1:21:22.585
or waving Confederate flags."
And I said...

1:21:24.210 --> 1:21:27.335
"Well, in your-- in your dream,
who-- who was president?"

1:21:27.418 --> 1:21:29.377
And she said, "Me." (CHUCKLES)

1:21:29.460 --> 1:21:32.543
And then I just got so busy...

1:21:32.627 --> 1:21:36.502
'cause we admitted 58 more
COVID patients in one day,

1:21:36.585 --> 1:21:41.835
and I-- I didn't have time
to check in on Miriam...

1:21:44.418 --> 1:21:46.585
because... (KISSES TEETH)

1:21:46.669 --> 1:21:50.377
four nurses tested positive
and were quarantined.

1:21:50.460 --> 1:21:52.627
I had one patient
that was giving birth...

1:21:54.627 --> 1:21:57.168
and her husband wasn't allowed
in the delivery room,

1:21:57.251 --> 1:22:00.168
and another patient was dying,

1:22:00.251 --> 1:22:03.001
and I had to hold
the phone to his ear

1:22:03.085 --> 1:22:05.835
so that his family could
tell him that they loved him.

1:22:08.669 --> 1:22:11.460
And the only thing that was
getting me through it was...

1:22:13.543 --> 1:22:14.543
her.

1:22:17.085 --> 1:22:18.627
Like, Miriam's gonna make it...

1:22:20.293 --> 1:22:22.293
'cause God wouldn't dare.

1:22:25.585 --> 1:22:27.210
Then the next morning,
she's even better.

1:22:27.293 --> 1:22:28.752
We don't need a ventilator.

1:22:28.835 --> 1:22:31.960
And I asked the doctor
if she can be discharged,

1:22:32.043 --> 1:22:34.877
and-- and he says,
"Yes, this afternoon."

1:22:35.669 --> 1:22:37.794
And I tell myself, "Okay...

1:22:37.877 --> 1:22:41.335
(INHALES)
This is what hope looks like."

1:22:43.168 --> 1:22:48.001
Later, just-- just after 2:00,
I get to Miriam's room...

1:22:49.043 --> 1:22:52.210
with a wheelchair,
and I'm picturing myself...

1:22:53.585 --> 1:22:55.418
wheeling her
out the front door...

1:22:56.710 --> 1:22:58.085
into the fresh air...

1:23:02.543 --> 1:23:04.502
while everybody cheers.

1:23:09.460 --> 1:23:11.210
But she's gone.

1:23:13.543 --> 1:23:16.210
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

1:23:17.043 --> 1:23:18.085
A stroke.

1:23:25.377 --> 1:23:26.835
She couldn't breathe.

1:23:28.752 --> 1:23:30.210
We tried everything.

1:23:33.418 --> 1:23:36.168
I didn't even have enough time
to call her daughter in Seattle,

1:23:36.251 --> 1:23:39.293
and she had a living will...

1:23:41.710 --> 1:23:43.085
but I wasn't there.

1:23:50.919 --> 1:23:52.585
I mean, I'm not her child.

1:23:54.001 --> 1:23:56.085
I'm not her family. (SNIFFLES)

1:23:58.335 --> 1:23:59.543
But I wasn't there.

1:24:02.752 --> 1:24:05.126
(SNIFFLES) Uh...

1:24:08.335 --> 1:24:10.543
(INHALES)
Over the next few weeks,

1:24:10.627 --> 1:24:13.335
things got... things got better.

1:24:14.710 --> 1:24:16.627
Fewer COVID patients. (SNIFFLES)

1:24:18.085 --> 1:24:19.126
Less death.

1:24:20.543 --> 1:24:22.168
They shut down
the Javits Center...

1:24:24.043 --> 1:24:26.919
and the navy hospital ship left,
and, uh...

1:24:28.460 --> 1:24:30.126
tomorrow, I'm going home.

1:24:33.794 --> 1:24:36.126
(SNIFFLES) I, uh...

1:24:38.210 --> 1:24:42.085
I met Miriam's daughter,
and she's so sweet. (SNIFFLES)

1:24:44.085 --> 1:24:47.627
She gave me Miriam's bracelet,
a Playbill,

1:24:47.710 --> 1:24:51.335
and a tote bag
for Planned Parenthood.

1:24:52.960 --> 1:24:55.794
(SNIFFLES) And she said
if Miriam was a Pharaoh,

1:24:56.877 --> 1:24:58.835
that's what would be
in her pyramid.

1:25:00.251 --> 1:25:05.126
And I ask her what she thinks
is gonna be on her tombstone...

1:25:06.293 --> 1:25:07.669
and she thought about it.

1:25:09.669 --> 1:25:13.335
And then at exactly
the same time...

1:25:14.377 --> 1:25:17.585
we both said, "Fuck you."

1:25:17.669 --> 1:25:21.669
(CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES)

1:25:28.460 --> 1:25:31.835
(INHALES) I keep thinking
about ways I can honor her

1:25:32.502 --> 1:25:33.877
and what would suit her.

1:25:37.210 --> 1:25:38.543
And what would she want?

1:25:40.960 --> 1:25:42.585
And I think
I've figured it out...

1:25:44.919 --> 1:25:47.502
but I'm gonna keep it
between Miriam and me.

1:25:48.835 --> 1:25:50.210
But I'll give you a hint.

1:25:53.043 --> 1:25:54.543
I'm not voting Independent.

